article.description: The Chicago Bulls posted a 92-81 triumph over the Cleveland Cavaliers.
article.headline: Cavs lose for second time in six games
article.linkText: Hinrich leads Bulls to another win over Cavs
article.story: ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Zydrunas Ilgauskas had 17 points and six rebounds, leading the Cleveland Cavaliers to a 104-88 preseason win over the Chicago Bulls on Saturday night. Reserve Dajuan Wagner added 14 points for Cleveland, and Jeff McInnis scored 13. Drew Gooden had 10 rebounds. Eddie Curry scored 21 points for Chicago. LeBron James contributed 11 points for Cleveland in 22 minutes, going just 3-of-10 from the field. He had four rebounds. "I played decent, I'm moving off the ball pretty good," James said. "I made a few shots, a couple fouls happened, and I cooled off." Ilgauskas made his first six shots and scored 15 points in the opening quarter, helping the Cavaliers to a 33-26 lead. The game remained tight well into the third period. McInnis made a pair of shots in the final 2:41 of the quarter to break a 74-all tie and put the Cavaliers ahead to stay. Cleveland scored the first 10 points of the fourth quarter for a 90-76 lead. Chicago missed its first nine shots of the period and went scoreless for 5:41. Cleveland center DeSagana Diop did not play because of a sprained finger. Eddie Robinson (toe) and Tommy Smith (right shoulder bruise) sat out for Chicago. The Bulls' Gary Trent (personal reasons) also missed the game.
